===============================================================================
NOTICE — Responsible use
===============================================================================
This section is a notice for users, not additional license terms.

DownMan is a general-purpose download manager. You alone are responsible for how
you use it — including compliance with the terms of service of any site you access,
the copyright and licensing of any content you download, and the laws of your
jurisdiction. DownMan does not circumvent DRM or other technical protection measures.


===============================================================================
Third-party components
===============================================================================
DownMan invokes and/or is built with third-party software under its own license:

  - aria2   (download engine, run as a subprocess)  — GPL-2.0-or-later with
            OpenSSL exception. Not bundled; a runtime dependency.
  - FFmpeg  (media muxing, run as a subprocess)     — LGPL-2.1+/GPL. Not bundled;
            a runtime dependency.
  - yt-dlp  (site media capture, fetched at runtime) — The Unlicense (public domain).
  - Tauri and the Rust/JavaScript libraries compiled into DownMan — permissive
            licenses (MIT / Apache-2.0 / BSD / ISC / etc.). See THIRD-PARTY-LICENSES.md.

AppImage builds additionally bundle the WebKitGTK and GTK runtime libraries under
the GNU LGPL (v2.1+). The LGPL permits replacing these libraries in the AppImage;
their source is available from the GNOME project and your distribution.
